<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">🔹 Staking Resources</h2>
<p class="mb-6">Years of staking led to a library of scripts and notes I originally built for myself. I’m now sharing them with the community here. <a href="/guides" target="_blank">Browse the site</a> and the public repo:
<a href="https://github.com/Stakers-space/staking-scripts" target="_blank" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">github.com/Stakers-space/staking-scripts</a>
</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">🔹 Guides including also minority chains (e.g., <a href="/gnosis" target="_blank" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">Gnosis</a>)</h2>
<p class="mb-6"><a href="/ethereum" target="_blank" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">Ethereum</a> is well‑documented; smaller ecosystems are not. Stakers.space fills that gap with clear, practical walk‑throughs. For example, Gnosis staking can be tricky to test due to limited client support / supported client features — our guides call out the gotchas.</p>


<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4">🔹 The Goal</h2>
<p class="mb-4">Put essential staking knowledge in one place, focused on safety and simplicity. What you’ll find:</p>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-10">
<li><strong>Step‑by‑step guides</strong> — 1‑page "from zero to running" and deeper, <a href="/clients" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">client‑specific guides</a>. See <a href="/ethereum-staking/full-guide" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">Ethereum</a> and <a href="/gnosis-staking/full-guide" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">Gnosis</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Multi‑chain & multi‑service setups</strong> — e.g., Ethereum + Gnosis on a single staking node; Solo Staking + StakeWise + Rocket Pool and so on.</li>
<li><strong>Client overviews</strong> — compatibility overviews for <a href="/ethereum-staking/clients" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">Ethereum</a> and <a href="/gnosis-staking/clients" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">Gnosis</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Emergency procedures</strong> — proven steps for common incident scenarios.</li>
<li><strong>Client‑side encrypted Account</strong> — monitor validators and keep node details private: <a href="/account" class="text-emerald-700 hover:underline">stakers.space/account</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Automation scripts</strong> — hard‑earned fixes to recurring issues.</li>
</ul>

<section class="rounded-2xl border p-6 mb-12">
<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">About the Dashboard</h3>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-800">
<li><strong>What it tracks:</strong> validator statuses, node inventory, service configs, notes, and URLs you rely on.</li>
<li><strong>Encryption:</strong> all sensitive fields are encrypted locally in your browser using your password before anything is saved. We can’t read your stored data.</li>
<li><strong>Portability:</strong> of your encrypted data so you can move between machines safely.</li>
<li><strong>No tracking:</strong> no analytics; only technical cookies for sign‑in/session.</li>
</ul>
